.Dd June 24, 2026
.Dt SNIFF 8
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm sniff
.Nd minimal packet sniffer
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl v
.Op Fl c Ar count
.Op Fl w Ar file
.Fl I Ar interface
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility captures and inspects L2, L3, and L4 network traffic on a specified interface. It relies solely on native
.Dv AF_PACKET
and BPF sockets without external dependencies.
.Pp
The options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl c Ar count
Stop after receiving
.Ar count
packets.
.It Fl I Ar interface
Specify the network interface to sniff on. This option is required.
.It Fl w Ar file
Write captured packets to a PCAP format
.Ar file
for later analysis with tools like Wireshark or tcpdump.
.It Fl v
Increase verbosity. Can be specified multiple times up to 3 (e.g.
.Fl vvv ) .
Default output displays MAC and IP layer summaries.
Level 1
.Pq Fl v
shows L4 headers (TCP, UDP, ICMP).
Level 2
.Pq Fl vv
shows L4 headers and a payload hex-dump.
Level 3
.Pq Fl vvv
shows L4 headers and a full packet hex-dump including data link headers.
.El
.Sh AUTHORS
The
.Nm
utility and the knetutils suite were written by
.An kurumi .
